com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport
Class UserSecurityDimension

java.lang.Object
  com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport.UserSecurityDimension

public final class UserSecurityDimension
extends Object

A specification of the roles or access rights that a particular user has for a particular SecurityDimension.

For example, for a SecurityDimension named "Security Classification", a user may have the "Secret" role. Alternatively, for a SecurityDimension named "Compartment", they may have access rights to both "Operation A" and "Operation B".

A user should have a UserSecurityDimension for each SecurityDimension in the active schema.

Since:
1.0

public UserSecurityDimension(String dimensionId,

Constructs a new UserSecurityDimension.

Parameters:
dimensionId - A String containing the identifier of the SecurityDimension that this UserSecurityDimension refers to.
values - Strings containing the SecurityDimension values that the user with this UserSecurityDimension has. These must be valid values of the SecurityDimension identified in dimensionId. If SecurityDimension.isOrdered() is true for the SecurityDimension identified in dimensionId, this should contain a single value.

getValues

public List<String> getValues()
Gets Strings containing the SecurityDimension values that the user with this UserSecurityDimension has.

If SecurityDimension.isOrdered() is true for the SecurityDimension identified by getDimensionId(), there will be a single String. If SecurityDimension.isOrdered() is false, multiple Strings will be returned in alphabetical order.

Returns:
See above.
